text: Bolshaya Oka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Bolsheokinsky Selsoviet, Mechetlinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 1,064 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 16 km from Bolsheustyikinskoye. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mechetlinsky District
title: Bolshaya Oka
